MURPHY, Respondent, v. GRAHAM, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. May 9, 1893.) Appeal from judgment on report of referee. Action by Michael Murphy against Hugh Graham, as executor of William Carroll, deceased, for services rendered deceased.

Argued before MAYHAM, P. J., and PUTNAM and HERRICK, JJ.

Thomas O’Connor, for appellant. Isaiah Fellows, Jr., for respondent. HERRICK, J.

The questions involved in this case are entirely of fact, and, while there is a conflict of evidence, there is evidence to sustain the findings of the referee, and I can find no sufficient reason to reverse such findings. The judgment should be affirmed, with costs.
